Last weekend I introduced @samuelmilbank to the cinematic masterpiece “Don’t Tell Mom the Babysitter’s Dead” 😄Is Sue Ellen Crandell to thank for my year-round love of red and green together?? 
❤️💚 #redandgreen #notjustforxmas #generalapparelwest #imrightontopofthatrose #icantbethehubofyourcommunicationnetwork

I don’t think decorators should be too sentimental, because lives change and clients move constantly. But I do get that way about discontinued fabrics! I should’ve bought up all remaining stock of the weird scenic floral on this throw pillow (far left) 😢 It had what Sam calls a Bridge to Terabithia!!

What a joy it is to know Alex Papachristidis @alexsviewpoint, who celebrated his 60th birthday in great style last night at the Colony Club. Gardenias and topiaries a go-go courtesy of @david_monn 😍💚💚 and tunes by DJ @marjoriegubelmann 🎶 Alex’s outsized personality, chic and wit are matched only by his even bigger heart, especially when it comes to helping animals 🐶 His supportive words to a (slightly) younger decorator, yours truly, have always meant so much 🌠🌠
A friend’s house I helped decorate, though I can’t take credit for the beautiful garland 💚

Earlier this week at Casa Cruz … every year we try out a new swish (flash?) spot for the NO INC. holiday luncheon 🤩 In 2022 we settled into our new office, bid farewell to @tara_mccauley as she started her own firm, and tackled some exciting projects! I am beyond grateful to my team—Elhaam, Augusta, Nuala, and Caroline—for their hard work, dedication and sense of humor. And grateful for the trust of our clients, and for the support of all the vendors, craftspeople, editors, and other talented folks who make our work shine 🙏 Wishing everyone the happiest and healthiest holiday season and a fabulous 2023 🥂🍾🥳

Yesterday I sold our house 🥲 This  was a seven-year project, although I just started posting it recently. When I was a little boy I didn’t understand why my parents, a hearing-impaired teacher and a scientist/inventor, could not buy up all the historic homes in our neighborhood and fix them up. So that became my mission! This house found ME when I needed it most. I am so grateful for this experience, and for everyone involved, to make our house ready for its new owners, and for all the happy memories made here. Sam and I are already working on a new project that we can’t wait to share. 💚

The time has come … for you to bargain shop … for. your. LIFE!!!
There’s still time to buy tickets for Housing Works’ Design on a Dime {LINK IN BIO}, where 50+ of my most talented friends and colleagues create gorgeous rooms where everything is for sale, at INSANELY low prices! April 20-22 at the Met Pavilion in NYC 🌟 If you’ve tried to shop for a sofa lately you can compare … this one is 1200 bucks! Seriously, Housing Works is leading the fight to eradicate HIV / AIDS and homelessness: that’s why I support this cause and I hope you will too!! Sam and I have started sleeping at #thedutchessfolly while pretending to enjoy the new roof, boiler, water heater, abated asbestos and other necessary improvements 🫠 The new bathroom is really something though 🚽 Yesterday movers showed up four hours early with the contents of our former (tiny) house, while I was shopping in Connecticut. When I came back @samuelmilbank had staged our “library” just so … I am lucky! 💚 #countryhouse #GreekRevival #renovation #preservation #workinprogress #campingout #ish #notglamping

Cheers to my friend @therobertrufino, who just ended a glorious run at @housebeautiful to start his own business 🌟 This week I learned I’m not the only decorator who calls him Maestro, and with good reason: For decades Robert has conducted a symphony of luxury brands, magazines, houses, editorials, closets (!) and so much more. Once we were at a photo shoot 20 miles from the nearest gas station. With zero irony he announced: “I need a celadon vase about 10 inches high, with a 2 inch-wide neck.” 😭 That commitment to beauty paired with his Energizer work ethic inspires us all. Thank you and biggest congrats, Count Rufino 💚💚💚
📸 @thomasloof

When the contents of this Manhattan Beach, California house traveled to the Hamptons last summer I waited on the front lawn, checking my mental inventory. A few key pieces had gone missing. I asked the client “Where is our other green @christopherspitzmiller lamp?” “I don’t know, my sister might have it.” “WELL GET IT BACK FROM HER WE NEED THAT LAMP!!” I’m dramatizing for effect but a decorative lighting plan can make or break your whole experience 😅

The back of our house stresses me out! While the little 1.5-story section dates to the 1700s, it retains no original character ☹️. At some point a wonky connector was added to cover access to the basement and main house. And don’t get me started on the massive oil tank! Sam and I are thinking a Greek Revival porch loosely based on this house in Westerly, RI (via Zillow!). But should it be glazed, screened, or open? And its stairs will run the whole width … #decisions #TheDutchessFolly #GreekRevival #1836 #renovation #preservation #restoration #HudsonValley @samuelmilbank
